						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is left incomplete. It seems to record the merger of two villages Śembiyanmādēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam and Araṇkalakki-chaturvēdimaṅgalam founded by the Milāḍu chiefs Irāmadēvan Paṭṭālakaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikramaśōḻa-Malāḍuḍaiyāṉ and Siddovaḍavaṉ-Gāmuṇḍaṉ (?) <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uttamaśōḻa-Malāḍuḍaiyāṉ respectively in the 15th year of Uttama-Chōḷadēva, and probably their gift to the temple in this year. Mention is made of a princess (?) by name Pūdi Parāntakadēviyār.</p>						

						</summary>
